						<summary>

						<p>MADRAS.</p>						

						<p>On the base of a Jaina image in the Archaeological Showroom in the Government Museum.</p>						

						<p>••• ••• ••• •••••</p>						

						<p>This inscription opens with a salutation to Śāntinātha and contains a single verse in <hi rend="italic">Śardūlavikrīḍitam</hi> in the Sanskrit language recording the installation and consecration of the image of Śānti-Jina by a cheif referred to as Sāḷvēndra and Sāḷva-nṛipa.</p>						

